	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasPriority> 1 ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "the actual failing tests were test_read_acts_json_format and test_json_output_validates_against_schema, not the CI. read acts moved from a plain JSON array (orphaned to_value path in lib.rs:94, now confirmed dead for core-seam to sweep) to a JSON-LD document, and the OutputMode enum renamed the value to json-ld, but the tests still passed the old value json and asserted an array. CONFIRMED: tests follow the code to the single JSON-LD contract; json stays as an alias for jq ergonomics. principle agreed — one semantic output contract, alternate shapes (e.g. a --flatten/--no-context view dropping @context to emit the bare @graph array) are config views on that one pipeline, never a parallel serializer. the flatten view is deferred (YAGNI) until real scripting friction appears" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "fix the real \"jsonld tests failing\" — stale json output contract in clearhead-cli" ;
