	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-03T09:02:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb35-7c28-9704-bfb7efbd714d> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb35-7c28-9704-bfb7efbd714d" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "sweep the remaining naive workspace-data writes" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "plan.rs writes .ics with fs::write, charter.rs writes charter markdown in three places, archive.rs writes the completed file directly — route each through durability::atomic_write. exempt: write_or_print user-directed output, init.rs one-time bootstrap, gen_man. SEQUENCED after the caldav reconcile shell because its step 1 lifts the plan.rs mirror-path logic into core — sweeping plan.rs first would collide with that move" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001775> <urn:uuid:019f12d4-4f7c-7bc2-9c76-b048067d43e8> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T14:05:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb32-747c-aa98-37eabca59a11> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb32-747c-aa98-37eabca59a11" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "finish routing CLI writes through the durability primitive" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "write-durability closed with core's write sites converted, but the CLI's own save paths still call naive std::fs::write — every complete, update, cancel, and delete goes through commands/mod.rs save_file, so a crash mid-write can truncate a source-of-truth file. the crash-safety layer exists and is tested; the most common writes bypass it" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasPriority> 1 ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasSequentialChildren> true ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T14:22:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb37-7ef1-acb7-dc303a66d7ae> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb37-7ef1-acb7-dc303a66d7ae" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "unify action reference resolution on the core resolver" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "three implementations exist — core reference::resolve_reference is the real one, mutations::resolve_reference is a flat-list copy, and act_matches in commands/action.rs is a boolean check used by all mutating commands. act_matches breaks the spec's resolution order, an earlier name-contains match shadows a later exact alias, so complete can close the wrong action. NOTE 2026-07-11: this item and its three children were marked complete once already with no matching code or commit anywhere in the repo — caught during charter review and fixed for real this pass; see child descriptions for what actually landed" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasPriority> 1 ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> .
<urn:context:bug> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Context> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasContextIdentifier> "bug" .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb37-7ef1-acb7-dc303a66d7ae> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:bug> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasSequentialChildren> true ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T14:50:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb38-7614-b246-1d7d44c49322> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb38-7614-b246-1d7d44c49322" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "fix alias-beats-name precedence in mutating commands" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "this is the user-facing bug and lands first — find_act_mut must prefer full uuid, then short uuid, then alias, then name-contains across the whole list rather than first-match-any per action. landed as action_match_tier + find_best_match/_mut/_pos in commands/action.rs, replacing the OR'd boolean action_matches for every call site that resolves identity (find_action_mut, show_action, delete_action); action_matches itself survives only as an existence-only check where identity doesn't matter. regression tests: commands::action::resolution_tests" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:bug> ;
	<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> <urn:uuid:019f268f-eb37-7ef1-acb7-dc303a66d7ae> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T14:50:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb3a-7e79-b865-ac4c25dcba48> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb3a-7e79-b865-ac4c25dcba48" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "delete act_matches and the mutations resolver, delegate to one implementation" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "complete, update, cancel, and delete resolve through the same code path as plan.rs and the LSP; the ActionList-level entry can live in core beside reference.rs if the DomainModel shape is too heavy for file-local commands. LANDED DIFFERENTLY: core's reference::resolve_reference deliberately excludes name-contains matching for actions (see its own doc comment) and cannot serve mutating commands as-is, so there was nothing to delegate to. What actually happened: mutations::resolve_reference/MatchType/ResolvedAction were dead code once find_plan_file/find_plan_file_for_mutation were deleted (their only callers) and got deleted with them; the real fix — precedence order — landed in place at commands/action.rs, the actual seam every mutating command goes through, not in core" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> , <urn:context:library> ;
	<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> <urn:uuid:019f268f-eb37-7ef1-acb7-dc303a66d7ae> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasSequentialChildren> true ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T14:50:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb3b-7adb-8fc6-1161be233e32> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb3b-7adb-8fc6-1161be233e32" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "port the alias-before-name regression test to the surviving seam" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "mutations.rs test_resolve_alias_before_name is the guard that documents the spec order — it must outlive the module it currently lives in. lands as commands::action::resolution_tests::alias_beats_earlier_name_contains_match, alongside two new tests for the uuid/short-uuid tiers the original test didn't cover" .
<urn:context:testing> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Context> ;
