	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T14:50:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb3f-7238-928f-7fcb123ba985> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb3f-7238-928f-7fcb123ba985" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "deduplicate workspace config between CLI and core" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "environment_reader::Config carries get_tag_ancestors, expand_tag, and expand_tags as character-for-character copies of WorkspaceConfig in core config.rs, including roughly ninety lines of duplicated tests — and core's copy is strictly better because it also has descendants_and_self" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasPriority> 2 ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T14:27:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb41-7389-aff1-6e7ff6cd43f0> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb41-7389-aff1-6e7ff6cd43f0" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "delete the dead tag-hierarchy methods and their copied tests" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "get_tag_ancestors, expand_tag, and expand_tags on environment_reader::Config had zero callers outside their own test module — every real call site already resolved through ctx.workspace_config() and core's WorkspaceConfig, and action.rs:549 needs descendants_and_self, which only exists on the core copy. reworded from \"delegate\" to \"delete\" during review since no delegation was needed. Config keeps loading, precedence, and cli_ fields" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
	<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> <urn:uuid:019f268f-eb3f-7238-928f-7fcb123ba985> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T14:27:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f2a95-9447-7069-9604-e39ef1535549> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f2a95-9447-7069-9604-e39ef1535549" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "delete the redundant per-action ActionSource" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "SourcedAction.source stamps a per-file value onto every action: load.rs:172 sets file_path to the same PathBuf MarkdownCharter.acts_file already holds (line 183), and .project is never read anywhere. the only two readers (graph/insert.rs:120, graph/jsonld.rs:51) already iterate charters, so they read the path from the enclosing group. 3 of 5 construction sites already pass dummy PathBuf::new(). delete ActionSource and the now-dead ActionRepository, drop the field, derive provenance from the file/charter group — the more proper structure surfaced by the doctor-inventory design 2026-07-03" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:library> , <urn:context:cli> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T14:36:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb44-7fcc-8d3d-bffd32ce2539> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb44-7fcc-8d3d-bffd32ce2539" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "delete the unused lib.rs and commands/mod.rs dead surface" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "merge_hashmaps, run_workspace_sql_query, and load_workspace_actions in lib.rs have zero callers outside their own module (the sql name is wrong regardless, it is SPARQL). find_plan_file and find_plan_file_for_mutation live in commands/mod.rs, not lib.rs as originally titled, and are equally dead. deleting those two removes the last production callers of mutations::resolve_reference, MatchType, and ResolvedAction, which then also become test-only and should go too — a dead-code chain the reference-resolution unification missed because it was hiding behind these two functions" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T14:51:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb45-749b-8142-8e1440b45eb8> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb45-749b-8142-8e1440b45eb8" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "make update_action use ActionUpdate and apply_updates or delete them" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "the struct-based update pattern in mutations.rs is good design lying dead while update_action pokes ten positional params and reimplements it inline — same call as PlanFields already proves in the argparser. done: extended ActionUpdate with scheduled_at and duration (the two fields update_action needed that it lacked), update_action now builds one ActionUpdate and calls apply_updates instead of six inline field pokes. behavior improvement as a side effect: state transitions through update now stamp completed_at like complete/cancel already do, which the old inline code did not do. verified end-to-end against a scratch workspace (priority, description, state+completed_at, scheduled_at, duration all confirmed)" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
