<urn:uuid:019f2ea2-6339-7f52-9fe6-0514e95e1522> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f2ea2-6339-7f52-9fe6-0514e95e1522" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "route read actions through the workspace loader" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "collect_all_actions lists files and parses each directly — no sidecar hydration, no journal recovery, no load findings — so the most-used read command sees a different workspace than every other command: created dates missing, an interrupted batch shows torn state any loading command would have healed, and load warnings are invisible. converge on the loader; a per-file fast path survives only if the trust benchmark action proves it matters. done: collect_all_actions and collect_workspace_actions (same bug, not named in the original title but identical pattern across the multi-workspace read path) now both route through clearhead_core::load_workspace, matching every other command. --file/--charter filtering now matches MarkdownCharter.actions_file against the requested path (via charter_root-join + canonicalize) instead of reading that one file directly — the fast path is gone per the note, since no trust-benchmark action exists to justify keeping it. .completed.actions still read directly per matching file (the loader deliberately excludes them, they are an archive not live state). verified end-to-end: sidecar-hydrated created_at now shows in read/show output (previously silently absent); malformed-file recovery now warns+continues instead of hard-failing (test_read_acts_file_fails_on_malformed_input renamed/updated to assert the new behavior); multi-workspace read verified manually across two scratch workspaces" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasPriority> 2 ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T15:18:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f5328-7865-7843-abd2-2c25505e47f1> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f5328-7865-7843-abd2-2c25505e47f1" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "add a guard so the durability write seam cannot silently reopen" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "deny std::fs::write under src/commands via clippy disallowed-methods or a small test that greps the tree. done: a grep-guard test (tests/no_naive_writes.rs), not clippy disallowed-methods — clearhead-cli has no CI wired up at all (only clearhead-core has a workflow, and it is workflow_dispatch-only), so a clippy lint nobody runs would be a guard in name only; a cargo test guard fires on every local test run regardless. walking src/commands/ turned up two fs::write call sites the original write-durability sweep note did not name: mod.rs write_or_print (user-directed --write output) and plan.rs:899 (export --output icalendar) — both legitimately exempt for the same reason as write_or_print, both added to the EXEMPT allowlist with reasons. verified the guard actually catches a regression: added a decoy std::fs::write in src/commands/action.rs, confirmed the test fails and names the exact file:line, then removed it" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasPriority> 2 ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T15:20:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f5328-b1d0-79d0-8d5c-1c20fe29d14e> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f5328-b1d0-79d0-8d5c-1c20fe29d14e" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "add close_subtree to core with tests" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "one function taking the action list, root id, closing state, and timestamp; returns the closed subtree for the caller to append to the completed file. collect_subtree_ids moves with it. done: clearhead_core::domain::{close_subtree, collect_subtree_ids} (re-exported at crate root), landed as free functions next to Action's impl block. close_subtree stamps completed_at for both Completed and Cancelled states, matching the CLI's current inline behavior exactly — no cancelled_at field exists yet (action-lifecycle charter, still not-started); user decided to build now and accept a follow-up tweak rather than block on it. 5 unit tests covering subtree collection (root+descendants, leaf-only), state stamping, parent detachment, and that source actions are left untouched" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:library> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T15:25:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f5328-b282-7a01-b519-6fd3d3fc8fd3> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f5328-b282-7a01-b519-6fd3d3fc8fd3" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "collapse complete_action and cancel_action onto it" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "both become thin callers passing Completed or Cancelled; dry-run and messaging stay in the command layer. done: extracted close_action_subtree in commands/action.rs, taking closing_state plus present/past-tense verb strings (complete/Completed, cancel/Cancelled) since simple string-suffix derivation breaks on cancel -> cancelled (double l). complete_action and cancel_action are now two-line callers. also deleted the CLI-local collect_subtree_ids (now a pure duplicate of core's) and routed delete_action onto clearhead_core::collect_subtree_ids too, so all three mutating commands share one subtree-walk implementation. verified end-to-end against a scratch workspace: complete/cancel with children stamps completed_at, detaches parent_id, moves the whole subtree to .completed.actions, dry-run and success messages byte-for-byte match the pre-refactor wording" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T15:27:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f5328-899f-7e32-ac04-3fc36b28d123> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f5328-899f-7e32-ac04-3fc36b28d123" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "move subtree-close semantics into core" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "what complete means (close the descendants, stamp completed_at, detach parents, move to the completed file) is business logic implemented inline in the CLI while core claims to own it. complete_action and cancel_action are fifty-line twins differing only in the target state. reopened 2026-07-11: originally marked complete but verification during charter review found no close_subtree function anywhere in clearhead-core, and complete_action/cancel_action in commands/action.rs are byte-for-byte unchanged from the pre-completion description — no commit, no stash, no other branch has this work" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasPriority> 2 ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:library> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T15:27:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb4b-7b05-93be-92418918c451> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb4b-7b05-93be-92418918c451" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "convert the command layer to anyhow Result with context" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "mechanical sweep, best done file-by-file after the seam work above so it does not conflict with everything. done: converted every commands/*.rs signature (80 sites across 12 files) plus main.rs/dispatch from Result<T, String> to anyhow::Result<T>. map_err(|e| e.to_string()) sites became bare ? (WorkspaceError/ParseFailure/ArchiveCharterError/etc. all implement std::error::Error, anyhow converts them for free). map_err(|e| format!(\"doing X: {}\", e)) sites became .context(\"doing X\")/.with_context(...) — same message, but now anyhow chains the source error's own Display underneath instead of string-interpolating it, so nested failures show their full cause chain. Err(format!(...))/Err(string) became anyhow::bail!(...). A few core functions (format, format_as_icalendar, run_workspace_raw_query) still return Result<T, String> directly rather than a typed error, so those sites use .map_err(|e| anyhow::anyhow!(e)) instead of .context() — context requires the source to impl std::error::Error. main.rs prints the full chain via anyhow's Debug format ({:?}) instead of just the top message. found and deleted commands/complete.rs along the way — an entire dead module (complete_action/CompletionResult) with zero callers anywhere, superseded by commands/action.rs's complete_action long ago. verified: full workspace build+test clean (all features, examples, bins), zero warnings, manually confirmed the new single-line and chained error output end-to-end against a scratch workspace" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T16:03:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb49-7e1b-9e4b-6f93ebf25fda> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb49-7e1b-9e4b-6f93ebf25fda" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "adopt structured errors at the CLI boundary" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "one hundred twenty-five Result String sites re-stringify errors core already types with thiserror, burying every call in map_err format noise. anyhow with context at the binary layer deletes most of it and improves the error output — the largest same-behavior-less-code win in the review" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasPriority> 3 ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#requiresContext> <urn:context:cli> ;
	<https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001868> <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Completed> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasCompletedDateTime> "2026-07-11T16:03:00-07:00"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<urn:uuid:019f268f-eb4c-7384-b316-a3b880291ab4> a <https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#Action> ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasUUID> "019f268f-eb4c-7384-b316-a3b880291ab4" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "record the call-site sweep done-gate in the process spec" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "the durable lesson — a core capability is not done until CLI call sites are swept onto it and a guard exists — belongs in specifications process.md so future charters inherit it instead of rediscovering it. done: added an Engineering Process section to specifications/process.md with a Call-Site Sweep Done-Gate subsection, naming the 2026-07-11 false-completion incident concretely (precedence bug, subtree-close semantics, durability guard all marked done with no matching commit) and the four-step gate: implement once, sweep every call site, add a proportional guard, verify the claim against git log/source rather than trusting the description" ;
	<https://clearhead.us/vocab/actions/v4#hasPriority> 3 .
